IRANIAN NUCLEAR CRISIS WORSENS
2011-12-30 11:31:55 GMT
On Nov. 8, the UN nuclear watchdog IAEA published a report, claiming that Iran had made plans to develop nuclear explosive devices and had been carrying out related experiments at least before 2003.Although Teheran categorically rejected the allegation, Western countries such as the United States, Britain and France took the lead in imposing tougher sanctions on Iran, sparking anger among Iranian people. Protesters broke into the British embassy compound in Tehran on Nov. 29.The latest confrontation between the West and Iran had added fuel to the thorny Iranian nuclear issue.
